pwhm: add lean getStationStatsBrief() RPC for the per-poll monitor stats path

wld publishes every associated station under
WiFi.AccessPoint.{i}.AssociatedDevice.{i}. and exposes getStationStats(), which
the prplMesh monitor polls ~1/s per radio. After patch 0901 removed the static
datamodel write-back from that path, the dominant remaining cost is the reply
builder itself: s_addStaStatsValues() re-marshals the entire AssociatedDevice
datamodel object -- about 70 parameters, including all the static identity and
capability strings -- plus the whole AffiliatedSta sub-list, back out of the
datamodel via swla_dm_getObjectParams() for every station on every poll. At 114
associated stations that read-back is ~13.7% of wld CPU, and the consumer reads
almost none of it.

The sole consumer of this RPC is the prplMesh monitor (mon_wlan_hal_whm
read_station_stats), which parses only 14 volatile fields per station and reads
nothing from AffiliatedSta or the static block. Every other datamodel consumer
reads the AssociatedDevice.{i}.* objects directly, not this RPC return value.

Add a dedicated getStationStatsBrief() RPC alongside the unchanged
getStationStats(). It keeps all datamodel writes -- it still pulls from the
driver and still calls wld_vap_sync_assoclist() (object create/remove,
wld_ad_syncStats() volatile refresh and the 0901-gated wld_ad_syncInfo()), so
datamodel freshness and lifecycle for TR-181 consumers are identical -- but
builds the RPC reply directly from the live T_AssociatedDevice, emitting only
the 14 fields the monitor consumes. No swla_dm_getObjectParams(), no
AffiliatedSta, no ObjectIndex.

The shared driver-pull/sync prologue is factored into s_addStaStatsPrologue()
called by both reply builders so they cannot drift. The 14-field value
expressions, types and the alias quirks (TxErrors from TxFailures, RxErrors from
RxFailures emitted as uint64) are copied verbatim from s_setAssocDevStatsParams()
-- the comment in s_addStaStatsValuesBrief() points back at it so the duplicated
mapping is kept in sync. Because the prologue still runs wld_ad_syncStats(),
pAD == datamodel at reply time, so the lean reply carries the same values a full
read-back would.

The 14-key set (MACAddress, TxBytes, RxBytes, TxErrors, RxErrors, TxPacketCount,
RxPacketCount, TxUnicastPacketCount, Tx_Retransmissions, LastDataDownlinkRate,
LastDataUplinkRate, DownlinkBandwidth, SignalNoiseRatio, SignalStrength) is a
tight cross-repo contract with the prplMesh monitor. Adding a 15th field is a
conscious two-repo change (pwhm emitter + monitor read_station_stats); the
paired prplMesh patch flips the monitor call site to getStationStatsBrief().

getStationStats() and its full reply are left byte-for-byte unchanged, so any
other (rare) caller is unaffected.

Upstream-Status: Pending

